The alliance ambushed the Norwegian King Olaf and won the battle thanks to their superior numbers with 70 ships to Norways just 11 ships. After the battle the Jarls of Lade ruled Norways as a fief of Denmark and Sweden.

Fin shot; and the arrow hit the middle of Einar's bow just at the moment that Einar was drawing it, and the bow was split in two parts.
